<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  iOS entitlements for Flixsy.

  com.apple.developer.networking.multicast lets the pure-Dart discovery
  channels send/receive SSDP multicast (Roku, webOS, Samsung). It is a
  RESTRICTED entitlement: Apple must approve a request before a provisioning
  profile can carry it — https://developer.apple.com/contact/request/networking-multicast

  THIS FILE IS NOT WIRED INTO THE BUILD YET. Adding it to code signing before
  Apple grants the entitlement makes signing fail. Once Apple approves and the
  provisioning profile is regenerated, wire it by setting, on every Runner
  build configuration in ios/Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:

      CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS = Runner/Runner.entitlements;

  (Or in Xcode: Runner target -> Signing & Capabilities -> + Capability ->
  Multicast Networking, which sets the same build setting.)

  mDNS for Android TV (_androidtvremote2._tcp) does NOT need this entitlement —
  it works through NSBonjourServices in Info.plist alone.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.developer.networking.multicast</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
